The Student Loan MarketingAssociation, Sallie Mae, announced an offering of 100 mln dlrsof three-year fixed rate notes redeemable at maturity in theU.S. dollar equivalent of 145.2 mln Australian dlrs.    It said the 12.125 pct obligation will be priced at par andsold in the United States in a public offering managed byMorgan Stanley.    Interest payments on the notes will be made semiannually inU.S. dlrs starting on Sept 20, 1987, Sallie Mae said.    It added that the notes are due march 20, 1990.    Sallie Mae said it will enter into a separate currencyexchange agreement to convert the principal payment at maturityfrom Australian dollars to U.S. dollars.    It said the notes will be issued in registered form and beavailable in denominations of 10,000 U.S. dlrs and in 5,000 dlrincrements above that amount.    Sallie Mae said proceeds will be used for general corporatepurchases. Reuter&#3;